solution: ```class Solution:
    def strangePrinter(self, s: str) -> int:
        n = len(s)
        if n == 0:
            return 0
        dp = [[0] * n for _ in range(n)]
        for i in range(n - 1, -1, -1):
            dp[i][i] = 1
            for j in range(i + 1, n):
                if s[i] == s[j]:
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i][j - 1]
                else:
                    min_val = float('inf')
                    for k in range(i, j):
                        min_val = min(min_val, dp[i][k] + dp[k + 1][j])
                    dp[i][j] = min_val
        return dp[0][n - 1]
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^3)
space complexity: O(n^2)
energy implications: MEDIUM
explanation: Uses dynamic programming on substrings; dp[i][j] stores the minimum prints for s[i..j]. When endpoints match, reuse the left part; otherwise split at every k and take the minimum sum.

